🔥 Day 20 of 30 Days SQL Challenge

Today I solved Problem #627 – Swap Salary on LeetCode.

🧠 Problem:

We are given a table with a column sex containing only:

'm' (male)

'f' (female)

The task was simple but tricky:

 👉 Swap all 'm' to 'f' and all 'f' to 'm'

 ❌ Without using a temporary table.

💡 Key Learning:

This problem teaches the power of the CASE statement in SQL.

Instead of creating extra tables or variables, we can update values conditionally in a single query:



UPDATE Salary

SET sex = CASE

            WHEN sex = 'm' THEN 'f'

            ELSE 'm'

          END;



🚀 Takeaway:

Sometimes the cleanest solution is using conditional logic smartly within the same column.

Consistency > Complexity.

